The funny thing is the fat rapist dude is actually a pretty accurate depiction of what knights were really like. The image of the knight we have today is actually heavily romanticized. In actual truth, knights were like the medieval version of spoiled rich brats (only much worse). Sure they had a 'Code of Chivalry'. But conveniently, it was only applied when dealing with people of (or above) their own station. Basically, they liked to spend their time throwing their weight around - bullying, looting, and raping peasants/serfs whenever they were not busy trying to kill each other.  The more you know...
